    <h1>Module 1: Introduction to Digital Marketing</h1>
  
    <h2>What is Digital Marketing?</h2>
    <p>Digital marketing is a broad range of marketing techniques that use technology or the Internet to connect with customers.</p>
  
    <h2>Key Digital Marketing Channels</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</li>
      <li>Pay-Per-Click (PPC) Advertising</li>
      <li>Social Media Marketing (SMM)</li>
      <li>Content Marketing</li>
      <li>Email 1  Marketing</li>
      <li>Affiliate Marketing</li>
      <li>Mobile Marketing</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>The Evolution of Digital Marketing</h2>
    <p>Digital marketing has evolved significantly over the years, from the early days of the internet to the present age of AI and automation.</p>
  
    <h2>Key Concepts in Digital Marketing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Target Audience:** Identifying and understanding your ideal customer.</li>
      <li><strong>Customer Journey:** Mapping the customer's journey from awareness to purchase.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Marketing Funnel:** A visual representation of the customer journey.</li>
      <li><strong>Call to Action (CTA):** Encouraging users to take a desired action.</li>
      <li><strong>Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO):** Improving the conversion rate of your website or marketing campaign.</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>The Role of Digital Marketing in Modern Business</h2>
    <p>Digital marketing plays a crucial role in modern business by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Increasing brand awareness</li>
      <li>Improving customer engagement</li>
      <li>Driving sales and revenue</li>
      <li>Building brand reputation</li>
      <li>Measuring marketing ROI</li>
    </ul>
