    <h1>Module 2: Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</h1>
  
    <h2>Understanding Search Engines</h2>
    <p>Search engines like Google use complex algorithms to crawl, index, and rank websites.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Crawling:** Search engines send out spiders to discover new web pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Indexing:** Relevant content is added to the search engine's index.</li>
      <li><strong>Ranking:** Search algorithms determine the relevance and quality of pages to rank them in SERPs.</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>On-Page SEO</h2>
    <p>On-page SEO involves optimizing elements on your website:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Keyword Research:** Identify relevant keywords and use them strategically in your content.</li>
      <li><strong>High-Quality Content:** Create valuable, informative, and engaging content.</li>
      <li><strong>Meta Tags and Descriptions:** Write compelling meta titles and descriptions to attract clicks.</li>
      <li><strong>Header Tags:** Use H1, H2, H3, etc. tags to structure your content and improve readability.</li>
      <li><strong>Image Optimization:** Optimize image file sizes and use descriptive alt text.</li>
      <li><strong>URL Structure:** Use clean and descriptive URLs.</li>
      <li><strong>Internal Linking:** Link to relevant pages within your website.</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>Off-Page SEO</h2>
    <p>Off-page SEO involves building backlinks and improving your website's authority:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Backlink Building:** Acquire high-quality backlinks from other websites.</li>
      <li><strong>Social Media Marketing:** Promote your content on social media platforms.</li>
      <li><strong>Local SEO:** Optimize your website for local search queries.</li>
      <li><strong>Brand Building:** Build a strong brand reputation through consistent branding and messaging.</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>Technical SEO</h2>
    <p>Technical SEO involves optimizing the technical aspects of your website:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Website Speed:** Optimize website speed for faster loading times.</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile-Friendliness:** Ensure your website is mobile-friendly and responsive.</li>
      <li><strong>XML Sitemaps:** Create and submit XML sitemaps to help search engines discover your website's pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Robots.txt:** Use a robots.txt file to control how search engine crawlers access your website.</li>
      <li><strong>URL Structure:** Use clean and descriptive URLs.</li>
    </ul>
  
    <h2>Measuring SEO Success</h2>
    <p>Track key metrics to measure the effectiveness of your SEO efforts:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Organic traffic</li>
      <li>Keyword rankings</li>
      <li>Backlinks</li>
      <li>Domain authority</li>
      <li>Click-through rate (CTR)</li>
    </ul>
