  <h1>Module 5: Content Marketing</h1>

  <h2>What is Content Marketing?</h2>
  <p>Content marketing involves creating and sharing valuable, relevant, and consistent content to attract and retain a clearly defined audience and, ultimately, drive profitable customer action.</p>

  <h2>Why Content Marketing is Important</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Increased brand awareness</li>
    <li>Improved SEO</li>
    <li>Lead generation</li>
    <li>Customer engagement</li>
    <li>Brand reputation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Content Marketing Process</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Planning and Strategy:**
      <ul>
        <li>Identify your target audience</li>
        <li>Set clear goals</li>
        <li>Develop a content calendar</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Content Creation:**
      <ul>
        <li>Blog posts</li>
        <li>Articles</li>
        <li>Videos</li>
        <li>Infographics</li>
        <li>Ebooks</li>
        <li>Webinars</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Content Distribution:**
      <ul>
        <li>Social media sharing</li>
        <li>Email marketing</li>
        <li>Search engine optimization (SEO)</li>
        <li>Paid advertising</li>
        <li>Influencer marketing</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Measurement and Analysis:**
      <ul>
        <li>Track key metrics (website traffic, engagement, conversions)</li>
        <li>Use analytics tools (Google Analytics, etc.)</li>
        <li>Make data-driven decisions</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Types of Content</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Blog posts</li>
    <li>Articles</li>
    <li>Videos</li>
    <li>Infographics</li>
    <li>Ebooks</li>
    <li>Webinars</li>
    <li>Case studies</li>
    <li>Whitepapers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Effective Content Marketing Strategies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Keyword research</li>
    <li>Compelling headlines</li>
    <li>Engaging content</li>
    <li>Visual appeal</li>
    <li>Strong calls to action</li>
  </ul>
