  <h1>Module 8: Digital Marketing for E-commerce</h1>

  <h2>Understanding E-commerce</h2>
  <p>E-commerce involves buying and selling goods and services over the internet.</p>

  <h2>Key E-commerce Platforms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Shopify</li>
    <li>WooCommerce</li>
    <li>Magento</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>E-commerce Marketing Strategies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>**Search Engine Optimization (SEO):** Optimize product pages, website structure, and content for search engines.</li>
    <li>**Pay-Per-Click (PPC) Advertising:** Use Google Shopping Ads and social media advertising to drive traffic to your e-commerce store.</li>
    <li>**Email Marketing:** Send targeted email campaigns to nurture leads and drive sales.</li>
    <li>**Social Media Marketing:** Leverage social media platforms to build brand awareness and engage with customers.</li>
    <li>**Influencer Marketing:** Partner with influencers to promote your products.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Product Page Optimization</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Compelling product titles and descriptions</li>
    <li>High-quality product images and videos</li>
    <li>Customer reviews and ratings</li>
    <li>Clear calls to action</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>E-commerce Analytics</h2>
  <p>Track key metrics to measure the performance of your e-commerce store:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website traffic</li>
    <li>Conversion rate</li>
    <li>Average order value</li>
    <li>Customer lifetime value</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Mobile Commerce</h2>
  <p>Optimize your e-commerce store for mobile devices to cater to the growing number of mobile shoppers.</p>
