<body>
  <h1>Module 2: Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</h1>

  <h2>What is SEO?</h2>
  <p>SEO is the process of optimizing your website to rank higher in search engine results pages (SERPs).</p>

  <h2>How Search Engines Work</h2>
  <p>Search engines like Google use algorithms to crawl, index, and rank websites.</p>

  <h2>On-Page SEO</h2>
  <p>On-page SEO involves optimizing elements on your website, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keyword research and optimization</li>
    <li>High-quality content creation</li>
    <li>Meta tags and descriptions</li>
    <li>Header tags (H1, H2, etc.)</li>
    <li>Image optimization</li>
    <li>URL structure</li>
    <li>Internal linking</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Off-Page SEO</h2>
  <p>Off-page SEO focuses on building backlinks and improving your website's authority.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Backlink building</li>
    <li>Social media marketing</li>
    <li>Local SEO</li>
    <li>Brand building</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technical SEO</h2>
  <p>Technical SEO involves optimizing the technical aspects of your website for search engines.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website speed</li>
    <li>Mobile-friendliness</li>
    <li>XML sitemaps</li>
    <li>Robots.txt</li>
    <li>URL structure</li>
  </ul>
</body>
