  <h1>Module 4: Social Media Marketing</h1>

  <h2>What is Social Media Marketing?</h2>
  <p>Social media marketing involves using social media platforms to connect with your target audience, build brand awareness, and drive sales.</p>

  <h2>Popular Social Media Platforms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Facebook</li>
    <li>Instagram</li>
    <li>Twitter</li>
    <li>LinkedIn</li>
    <li>TikTok</li>
    <li>YouTube</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Creating a Social Media Marketing Strategy</h2>
  <p>A successful social media strategy involves:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>**Defining your goals:** Clearly outline what you want to achieve with social media.</li>
    <li>**Identifying your target audience:** Understand your ideal customer's demographics, interests, and behaviors.</li>
    <li>**Choosing the right platforms:** Select the platforms that align with your target audience and marketing goals.</li>
    <li>**Creating a content calendar:** Plan your content in advance to maintain consistency.</li>
    <li>**Creating engaging content:** Develop content that resonates with your audience and encourages interaction.</li>
    <li>**Building a strong social media presence:** Maintain a consistent brand voice and visual style.</li>
    <li>**Monitoring and analyzing:** Track key metrics to measure the effectiveness of your social media efforts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Social Media Advertising</h2>
  <p>Paid social media advertising allows you to reach a wider audience and achieve specific marketing goals. Popular platforms for paid advertising include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Facebook Ads</li>
    <li>Instagram Ads</li>
    <li>Twitter Ads</li>
    <li>LinkedIn Ads</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Social Media Listening</h2>
  <p>Monitoring social media conversations can help you identify trends, respond to customer inquiries, and manage crises.</p>

  <h2>Social Media Analytics</h2>
  <p>Track key metrics to measure the success of your social media efforts, such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Impressions</li>
    <li>Reach</li>
    <li>Engagement rate</li>
    <li>Click-through rate (CTR)</li>
    <li>Conversion rate</li>
