      margin-left: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Module 7: Analytics and Measurement</h1>

  <h2>The Importance of Analytics</h2>
  <p>Analytics is crucial for understanding your audience, measuring the effectiveness of your marketing campaigns, and making data-driven decisions.</p>

  <h2>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</h2>
  <p>Track key metrics to measure the success of your marketing efforts:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website Traffic</li>
    <li>Social Media Metrics</li>
    <li>Email Marketing Metrics</li>
    <li>PPC Metrics</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Web Analytics Tools</h2>
  <p>Use web analytics tools to gain insights into your website traffic and user behavior:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Google Analytics</li>
    <li>Adobe Analytics</li>
    <li>Hotjar</li>
    <li>Crazy Egg</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Social Media Analytics</h2>
  <p>Track the performance of your social media campaigns using platform-specific analytics tools and third-party tools like Hootsuite Insights and Buffer Analyze.</p>

  <h2>Email Marketing Analytics</h2>
  <p>Measure the effectiveness of your email campaigns by tracking metrics like:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Open rate</li>
    <li>Click-through rate</li>
    <li>Conversion rate</li>
    <li>Unsubscribe rate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>A/B Testing</h2>
  <p>Experiment with different variations of your marketing assets to optimize performance.</p>

  <h2>Data-Driven Decision Making</h2>
  <p>Use data to inform your marketing strategy and make data-driven decisions.</p>
