<body>
  <h1>Module 9: Affiliate Marketing</h1>

  <h2>What is Affiliate Marketing?</h2>
  <p>Affiliate marketing is a performance-based marketing strategy where businesses reward affiliates for each visitor or customer brought by their marketing efforts.</p>

  <h2>How Affiliate Marketing Works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Affiliate Sign-up:** Affiliates sign up for a program and get unique affiliate links.</li>
    <li><strong>Promotion:** Affiliates promote products or services through their website, blog, social media, or email.</li>
    <li><strong>Customer Referral:** When a customer clicks on an affiliate link and makes a purchase, the affiliate earns a commission.</li>
    <li><strong>Commission Payment:** The affiliate network tracks sales and pays commissions to affiliates.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Benefits of Affiliate Marketing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Increased Sales</li>
    <li>Reduced Marketing Costs</li>
    <li>Brand Awareness</li>
    <li>Scalability</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Choosing the Right Affiliate Program</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Identify your target audience</li>
    <li>Select relevant affiliate networks</li>
    <li>Evaluate affiliate programs based on commission rates, payment terms, and tracking methods</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Effective Affiliate Marketing Strategies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Content Marketing</li>
    <li>Email Marketing</li>
    <li>Social Media Marketing</li>
    <li>Influencer Marketing</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tracking Affiliate Performance</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Click-through rate (CTR)</li>
    <li>Conversion rate</li>
    <li>Earnings per click (EPC)</li>
    <li>Return on investment (ROI)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal and Ethical Considerations</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Disclosure</li>
    <li>Fair Practices</li>
    <li>Tax Implications</li>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>
