<body>
  <h1>Module 11: Digital Marketing for B2B</h1>

  <h2>Understanding B2B Marketing</h2>
  <p>B2B marketing involves promoting products and services to other businesses.</p>

  <h2>Key Differences Between B2B and B2C Marketing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Longer sales cycles</li>
    <li>Complex decision-making processes</li>
    <li>Focus on building relationships</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>B2B Content Marketing</h2>
  <p>Create high-quality content to attract and engage your target audience:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Whitepapers</li>
    <li>Case studies</li>
    <li>Webinars</li>
    <li>Blog posts</li>
    <li>Infographics</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>B2B Email Marketing</h2>
  <p>Nurture leads and build relationships through targeted email campaigns:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Welcome emails</li>
    <li>Product updates</li>
    <li>Thought leadership content</li>
    <li>Personalized email campaigns</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>B2B Social Media Marketing</h2>
  <p>Leverage platforms like LinkedIn, Twitter, and YouTube to connect with professionals and decision-makers.</p>

  <h2>B2B SEO</h2>
  <p>Optimize your website for search engines to attract organic traffic from B2B decision-makers.</p>

  <h2>B2B PPC Advertising</h2>
  <p>Use platforms like Google Ads and LinkedIn Ads to target specific industries and job titles.</p>

  <h2>Account-Based Marketing (ABM)**
  <p>ABM focuses on targeting specific accounts and tailoring marketing efforts to their needs.</p>

  <h2>Measuring B2B Marketing Success</h2>
  <p>Track key metrics such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Website traffic</li>
    <li>Lead generation</li>
    <li>Sales pipeline</li>
    <li>Customer lifetime value</li>
    <li>Return on investment (ROI)</li>
  </ul>
</body>
